Wilbur O. MORTON, Appellant, v. UNITED STATES of America, et al., and the State of Kansas et al., Appellees. No. 8711. United States Court of Appeals Tenth Circuit. Aug. 4, 1966. Alex T. Collins, III, for appellant. William E. Gandy, Asst. U. S. Atty. (Lawrence M. Henry, U. S. Atty. for District of Colorado, David I. Shedroff, Asst. U. S. Atty. for District of Colorado, on the brief), for appellees.

Before PHILLIPS, JONES* and SETH, United States Circuit Judges.

Of the Fifth Circuit, setting by designation.

 PER CURIAM.

The judgment of the district court is correct and is affirmed.
